A man was fatally shot in Adelphi, Md., on Thursday, police said. The shooting happened around 5:45 p.m. in the 1900 block of Laguna Road. When officers arrived, they found Ruben Garcia-Ramos with gunshot wounds to the upper body. Ramos, 37, of Adelphi, died at a hospital, officials said. The incident does not appear to be random, police said. Anyone with information is asked to call police at 1-866-411-TIPS. The D.C. area has seen 49 homicides so far this year, according to tracking by The Washington Post. Of those, 17 were in Maryland, including 12 in Prince Georgeâ€™s County. Correction: An earlier version of this story incorrectly stated the incident occurred in Hyattsville. 